an analysis of terms used for FCN in German, Anglophone and Russian literary criticism. Building on the perception of FCN as a phenomenon of interference between narrator’s and character’s text (text interference), this book analyses the function and applications of FCN in narratives written in German, English and Russian.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022)  aNarrative discourse.  apoint of view.  atext interference.0 cEPUBz97831107631640 cprintz978311076305840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076310240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110763102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110763102/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK